summary: This is a court subpoena issued by the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York to the Sacramento County Clerk/Recorder, commanding them to appear and produce a birth certificate for an unnamed individual in the case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell. The subpoena is dated August 27, 2021, and demands appearance on November 29, 2021.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: The defendant in the criminal case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell (20 Cr. 330 (AJN)), which is the subject of the subpoena.

persons.name: Audrey Strauss
persons.context: The United States Attorney for the Southern District of New York who signed the subpoena on August 27, 2021.

events.title: Scheduled Court Appearance for Document Production
events.description: The Sacramento County Clerk/Recorder is commanded to appear in court to produce a birth certificate for an unnamed individual as part of the case against Ghislaine Maxwell.

locations: 40 Foley Square, Courtroom 906, Borough of Manhattan, City of New York, New York
keyFacts: The U.S. Attorney's Office subpoenaed a birth certificate from Sacramento County for an unnamed individual as part of the Ghislaine Maxwell criminal case.
The subpoena was signed by U.S. Attorney Audrey Strauss on August 27, 2021.
The document production was scheduled for November 29, 2021, at the U.S. District Court in Manhattan.
The subpoena indicates ongoing investigative or evidentiary gathering in the Maxwell case as of late 2021.
Failure to comply with the subpoena is stated to constitute contempt of court with potential civil and criminal penalties.
